From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: PlazaMC <dev@plazamc.org>
Date: Fri, 17 Jul 2026 22:30:00 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] Linear region format support (per-world)

Adds the IRegionFile abstraction (org.plazamc.server.linear) and lets
RegionFileStorage create Linear v2 region files instead of MCA ones on a
per-world basis. The decision uses the world name from RegionStorageInfo:
worlds configured with format LINEAR in worlds.yml (or whose storage folder
already contains .linear files) read/write r.X.Z.linear files for chunk,
entity and POI data. Vanilla RegionFile implements IRegionFile too, so MCA
worlds keep working unchanged.

Linear V2 region format implementation:
Original license: GPL-3.0-only
Original projects:
  https://github.com/LuminolMC/Luminol
  https://github.com/xymb-endcrystalme/Abomination

